(Continued from above):
The juicy Fried Chicken Gyozas ($16) was a close runner-up.
Those who embrace the “more-is-better” approach to food, would probably be keen on the Fountain Wagyu, a surf ‘n’ turf creation that has seared Wagyu wrapped around a roll with tempura prawn, cream cheese, cucumber, tobiko, potato floss and housemade sriracha sauce ($34).
The Karaage Fried Chicken Thigh ($15) is one for die-hard fried chicken fans.

To check out the rest of the menu or to place an order, please tap on the link in @kinkibar’s bio.
